Package nl.naturalis.geneious

Class Settings

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.geneious.Settings
  • public class Settings
extends Object
    Provides access to the settings in the Tools -> Preferences tab. This class mainly exists to work around an awkward Geneious feature (if not bug) that makes directly accessing the options defined in the Preferences tab tricky. Notably tricky are the hidden settings. For these there are setters in this class that do not update the Settings object directly, but in stead update the corresponding option in the Preferences panel. That in turn triggers a change listener in the panel which updates the Settings object. That sounds like a round-about that could be short-circuited. Be careful if you try.
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman
